Indicator changes None (MER v2.6.1 to v2.7): Reporting level: Facility Reporting Semi-Annually frequency: How to use: This indicator measures the performance of HIV programs in scaling up TPT, with the goal of preventing progression to active TB disease among persons living with HIV (PLHIV). As part of a cascade from TX_CURR to TB screening (captured in TX_TB), this indicator will inform programs on the pace of scale-up, and the proportion will allow for monitoring of cohorts through completion of therapy.
